mkdir node-tests
cd node-tests

run:
npm-init
default values for everything. Simply press enter for all the questions

Note: 
1.npm i is similar to npm install
2.--save-dev is gonna save this package for development purpose only


npm i mocha@3.0.0 --save-dev

mkdir utils

Inside utils, create 2 files eg:
utils.js and utils.test.js

In your package.json under the scripts -> test, specify the execution path so that mocha looks into that pattern of files
mocha **/*.test.js



To run your test,
npm test

Watch and auto restart tests, run the below command in the terminal
nodemon --exec 'npm test'

To get this as a command, add a new line in package.json under scripts
"test-watch": "nodemon --exec 'npm test'"

test-watch is a custom script
To run a custom script, In terminal run the below command

npm run test-watch

Assertion Library
https://github.com/mjackson/expect

npm install expect@1.20.2 --save-dev




